 Oyo State House of Assembly Speaker, HON. ADEBO Ogundoyin. Photo/Facebook/HON. ADEBO Ogundoyin  Ogundoyin, a member of the ruling Peoples Democratic Party, emerged unopposed and with the unanimous voice vote of the 32-member assembly. The lawmaker representing Ona Ara state constituency Abiodun Mohammed Fadeyi was elected the deputy speaker. Oyo State House of Assembly has 26 members from the PDP, All Progressives Congress has five members while Action Democratic Party boasts of one member. An APC member is expected to be named the minority leader of the assembly. Details later. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .